review_blob: Really dark tones of chocolate, coffe, browned sugar and some dried fruits. Poors noce and dark with a foam that dissapears quickly. Taste takes the same as in the nose, and finnishes of with some hoppy grass flavours. Its a really good stout.

A bit of a let down, malty and sweet caramels in aroma. Follows in taste, but nothing really happends, its stays there. Perhaps too sweet, and definately would have been better with higher rates of hops.

This is a really good barley wine, will probably keep a few bottles for christmas evening. Malty with caramel and dried fruits in aroma, some hops but not much. Follows through in taste, lots of caramel, coffee, chocolate and browned sugar, even the fruit is there. The hops comes in second just as in the aroma.

Nice blueish color poors with a nice foam, not fully filttered, looks nice. Nose is full of blueberrys and clooudberry, aven some lingon and sea buckthorn follows throught. In taste the hoppy flavours balances it well, its a nice fruitinfused ipa, makes me think of christmas. Could have had a higher sourness and bitterness, but still a good one.
beer_name: BrewDog Hello, My Name Is Holy Moose

review_blob: Lots of caramel and grassy hops in the nose. Taste is malty with a strong citrus tone too much imo. Very high carbonated. Not a bad beer, but not as good as some of oppigrds other ones.

First impressions of flavour is well expected, not really any surprises there. Tastewise it starts of very similiar to a dark lager, lots of sweet notes, caramel, coffee chocolate. Then the hops takes over, a very nice followthrough. Its a good black ipa.
beer_name: Founders Dark Penance Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: This really is a excellent beer, aromas are there, taste and feel is there, yes, pretty much everything is! Poors nicely with a rich foam, lots of coffee and choclate notes, the pepper and vanilla comes in as a nice finnish.
A big fuity hop aroma. Loads and loads of fruits and grassy citrustones. Somewhat cloudy pale color. Taste is close to the nose, a rich bitterness acompanies the experience in a nice way. A good one.

A thick creamy head. The nose is exploding with fruits, mostly exotic ones. Same goes for taste, explosion of fruits after the initial hops, some sweetness, with taste of citrusfruits and excellent bitterness completes the brew, its such a nice one!

There is no surprises here, its a really good ipa, ticks all the boxes. Probably one of the best ipas ive tried considering if you take price into consideration. Congrats to ballast point for extremely good workmanship.

A really nice thick creamy head. Somewhat cloudy amber color. A really good aroma, full och fruit, grass, pine, citrus and even some dried fruits and caramel. And the taste that follows is the same, it starts of with a kick hoppy kick, and moves on to the malty caramel with a lingering fruit that transforms as it goes, fresh in the beginning, dried in the end. And all accompanied with a nice bitterness that is lasting a long time. Superd brew!

Pours a nice not fully filtered amber color. It looks really nice, gets the hopes up, as with the nose. Lots of fruit and hoppy notes. Though the taste is somewhat a dissapointment after the good start. Still not a bad brew, but could have been improved.
A nice unfiltered ipa with a thick head, Lots of fruity citrus tones in the nose. Could have wished for more fruit, or more bitterness. Still a nice brew for a warm summerday.

A really good brew where the amarillo and mosaic does the trick. One of the better swedish dipa ive tried. The mango is there in the nose, but not as much in taste, but it doesnt really matter, still a really good one!
Nice amber color with a thick head. Kicks in with a explosion of hops,as would be expected from this kind of dipa. No surprises, its a good brew.

The nose is full of fruity notes, if the taste would have followed it would have been a excellent saison, though it does not quite get all the way there, its still a really good one. Full of grass and citrus notes after all the fruit. Would have wished for a bit longer bitterness.

A nice full head. Chocolate, malt and fruity hops in the nose. Taste follows the same, first chocolate with rich malts, then fruity hops, could have wished for a bit more citrustones. But still a really nice one.

A really thick creamy head. First comes the brett, then it moves perfectly over to the mosaic hops, very smooth transition. Lots of tropical and citrus notes and the brett lingers on. Its a fantastic brew this one!

An excellent example of jigh amounts of malt and hops, without the overpowering sweetnes that can come from the malts. Lots of grassy fresh notes mixed with citrusfruits and some pines. Quite long lasting bittreness with a rich body. Its a nice everyday imperial ipa!

Slightly cloudy amber with a nice head. Could have been a jackpot with less filtration. Plenty of fruity tones, all exotic ones. Intensive and longlasting bittreness, really nice! A mild carbonation with a slightly sweet finish, top notch.

Black, with medium size, creamy, mocha head. Aroma is meaty, smoked ham and salty. A slightly creamy mouthfeel with low carbonation. Tastewise; a bit roasted, toffe, cocoa, coffee toffe lots of different smoked meat and sausages. Finishes off with a quite mild smoke, (not really ash) vanilla and a nice chocolate bitterness.
